The global wearable fitness trackers market can be segmented based on type, distribution channel, price range, and end-user. In terms of type, the market is divided into fitness bands and smartwatches. Fitness bands are primarily focused on tracking physical activity and health metrics, while smartwatches offer additional features such as smartphone connectivity and app integration. When considering the distribution channel, wearable fitness trackers are sold through both online and offline stores. Online stores provide convenience and a wide range of options, while offline stores offer customers the opportunity to try out the products before purchasing. Price range segmentation includes low, mid, and high ranges to cater to customers with varying budgets. Lastly, end-user segmentation includes men, women, and children, each with specific preferences and requirements in fitness tracking devices.

